(23, 'STAY HOME CAMPAIGN', 'stay-home-campaign', '<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">This pandemic has taught us how precious it is to spend some quality time with our family and loved ones. Home entertainment is something which helps bring together every family member and create some amazing joyful moments. As we’re going through a very rough phase, staying home with our family is the best thing we can do to protect ourselves and our family. To make your homestay worthwhile AKASH has launched “Stay Home Campaign”. Now, get TK 1,000 off on every new AKASH connection, and relish TV entertainment like never before.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Stay Home, Stay Safe and Enjoy the Best Quality TV Viewing Experience with your Family on AKASH!</span></strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Campaign Duration: </span></strong><span style=\"color:black\">June 28 to August 31, 2020 </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Terms and Conditions: </span></strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">During the campaign period, customers can enjoy AKASH Full Setup at only Tk. 4,499/- from any AKASH retailer outlets, online platform, partner e-Commerce websites and any other sales channel.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Discount will be applicable on multiple units of full setup purchase individually.  </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">There will be also discount on STB. The STB only would cost TK 2,999 instead of TK 3,199.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Corporate entities which are our subscriber by contracts/ are in invoicing relations or in rental modalities/models will continue at their original price point. </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">AKASH reserves all the right to change, extend and cancel the offer at any time.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"> </span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ): </span></strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">What is STAY HOME Campaign?</span></strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Ans: </span></strong><span style=\"color:black\">Anyone who buys a new AKASH Full Setup (1 Connection) within June 28- August 31 2020, can buy it with TK 4,499 from retail, online platform, e-Commerce websites and any other sales channel.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">How long is the duration of this STAY HOME Campaign?</span></strong> </span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Ans:</span></strong><span style=\"color:black\"> The STAY HOME Campaign is valid from June 28- August 31 2020. </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">If I purchase only STB, will I be eligible to pay the price of STAY HOME Campaign?</span></strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Ans: Yes! The price of TK 4,499 is for the full setup on a new connection. The STB only would cost TK 2,999</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">I\'m a current subscriber of AKASH. Am I eligible to participate STAY HOME Campaign?  </span></strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Ans: </span></strong><span style=\"color:black\">Yes, you will be eligible for the special price of Components. Full offer can be enjoyed for new connections only.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">I’m an employee of Beximco Group. Am I eligible?          </span></strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Ans: Yes, you are eligible. For further details and assistance, please contact with your respective key accounts manager.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">I am currently using AKASH Standard package am I eligible for the STAY HOME Campaign?</span></strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Ans: Yes! You can enjoy special price of Components only as the existing customer. Full offer can be enjoyed for new connections only. </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">I am currently using AKASH Lite package am I eligible for the STAY HOME Campaign?     </span></strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Ans:</span></strong><span style=\"color:black\"> Yes! You can enjoy special price of Components only as the existing customer. Full offer can be enjoyed for new connections only. </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">If I purchase through EMI on Online will I be eligible for the STAY HOME Campaign?</span></strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Ans: Yes! You can purchase a new connection (full setup) or STB at a special price under the STAY HOME campaign with EMI on Online.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">I am a retailer/Distributor of AKASH. Am I eligible for the STAY HOME Campaign?</span></strong>           </span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Ans:</span></strong><span style=\"color:black\"> Yes, you will be eligible for the special price of Components. Full offer can be enjoyed for new connections only.</span></span></span></p>\n', '1596218252-90887887.png', '1596218252-49693602.png', '', 'Promotional', 0, 0, 1, '2020-06-28 00:25:41', '2030-08-16 11:20:34', '2020-07-31 23:59:57', '2020-06-28 01:02:56', '', 123);
INSERT INTO `offers` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `description`, `thumb_image`, `banner_image`, `app_image`, `tags`, `show_in_app`, `show_buy_btn`, `state`, `start_time`, `end_time`, `updatedOn`, `createdOn`, `uda`, `serial`) VALUES
(24, 'VISA Card Campaign', 'visa-card-save', '<p>Get a 10% discount on your AKASH purchase via VISA card!</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;<strong><u>Offer and Eligibility Details</u></strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>10% off up to BDT 500</li>\n	<li>Offer applicable on first 2 transactions when you save a new Visa card</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong><u>Terms and Conditions</u></strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Customers must save their Visa Card while paying online.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Discount is only applicable for purchase of AKASH Connection (https://akashdth.com/buy-AKASH)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>One Visa card can only be used twice on each website to avail the offer. Maximum discount amount BDT 500 during the campaign period. The discount won&#39;t apply if the card is removed and then added again.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>If a customer has already saved their Visa card on a particular website at an earlier time (before March 24, 2020) or during the Save &amp; Save Campaign of 2020 (SSL), the same card won&rsquo;t be eligible to avail the offer from the same website. The discount is only applicable for customers who save a new Visa card on a particular website.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Payment must be made through SSLCOMMERZ Gateway. (below you&rsquo;ll find a snapshot of the Gateway<br />\n	<br />\n	<img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Payment must be made using a Visa card.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Only successful transactions will be counted.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Refunds will be processed as per the AKASH DTH policy.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>AKASH DTH will not be responsible for any card related security.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Offer valid till 30th September, 2020.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>AKASH DTH, Visa &amp; SSL Wireless reserves the right to modify the campaign terms &amp; conditions in any manner or cancel the entire campaign at any time without giving any prior notice.</li>\n	<li>AKASH DTH, Visa &amp; SSL Wireless reserves the right to cancel the discount if the particular transaction and/or the customer transaction behavior raises reasonable suspicion that the customer has abused the benefit of the campaign.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><u>Frequently Asked Questions</u></strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; <strong>What is the duration of this offer?</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Offer valid till 30th September, 2020.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp; </strong><strong>How can I avail this offer?</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; If you have a Visa card, you can enjoy the offer by saving your Visa Card while paying for AKASH &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Connection in AKASH&rsquo;s website.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Which gateway is applicable for the transaction for this campaign?</strong></p>\n\n<p>SSLCOMMERZ Payment Gateway is applicable for the campaign.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Which payment channels are allowed for this campaign?</strong></p>\n\n<p>Any Bangladeshi Local Visa card is allowed for this campaign. This includes both Debit and Credit cards of Visa</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>How many times can I avail the offers during the campaign period?</strong></p>\n\n<p>You can avail the offer twice from AKASH&rsquo;s website when you save your Visa card while paying online. However if you have already saved your card on a particular website at an earlier time (before March 24, 2020) or during the Save &amp; Save Campaign 2020 (SSL), the same card won&rsquo;t be eligible to avail the offer from that particular website.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Will I receive discount if my payment is successful?</strong></p>\n\n<p>If your payment is valid then AKASH &amp; SSLCOMMERZ recognizes the transaction as authentic, you will receive discount depending on the terms and conditions of the campaign. Otherwise, AKASH &amp; SSLCOMMERZ reserves the right to cancel the discount.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Is it safe to save my card information here?</strong></p>\n\n<p>Yes, it is absolutely safe to save your card information with SSLCOMMERZ. SSLCOMMERZ is authorized and licensed as a Payment Systems Operator (PSO) by Bangladesh Bank. SSLCOMMERZ is also PCI DSS compliant which is one of the most respected and recognized payment data security standard in the world. To achieve this compliance, an organization needs to go through quarterly tests and face rigorous audit through a Qualified Security Assessor (QSA). To continue with the compliance, SSLCOMMERZ goes through annual recertification process every year.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>When will my saved cards be used for transactions?</strong></p>\n\n<p>When you opt to save your card for AKASH, SSL will prompt you the saved cards which you can select for making a payment in other sites.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>How do you ensure that my saved card is used only by me?</strong></p>\n\n<p>When you are saving your card information during registration, SSL will verify you through Two Factor Authentication (2FA) to ensure that you own the card then map it with entered mobile phone number. Afterwards, whenever SSL gets your mobile phone number, they will verify your mobile phone number either through 2FA or an OTP before you can make any payments. SSL will keep track of your transactions and alert you if we detect any suspicious activities.</p>\n', '1595059181-2243269.jpg', '1595059181-10240139.jpg', '', 'Promotional', 0, 0, 1, '2020-07-18 13:55:35', '2030-08-16 11:20:34', '2020-07-18 13:59:42', '2020-07-18 13:59:42', '', 122);
INSERT INTO `offers` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `description`, `thumb_image`, `banner_image`, `app_image`, `tags`, `show_in_app`, `show_buy_btn`, `state`, `start_time`, `end_time`, `updatedOn`, `createdOn`, `uda`, `serial`) VALUES
(25, 'New User Interface (UI) & Personal Video Recording (PVR)', 'UI-PVR', '<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Genre Listing: </span></strong><span style=\"color:black\">This is a new addition into the UI. Now subscribers can view channels according to their genres. (One channel can be in multiple genres. For instance, DBC News HD is in HD, Bangladeshi Channels, and News genres). When subscriber selects a genre, he will be redirected to the program guide of only the channels of that genre.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Help Page: </span></strong><span style=\"color:black\">The &ldquo;Help&rdquo; page has been enhanced with the inclusion of Subscriber Name, RMN (Registered Mobile Number), Activated Package, Base Package Expiry, Balance etc. Info.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:#000000\">After recharging account or updating any other account or billing-related information, it might take up to 30 minutes for the &ldquo;Help Page&rdquo; to get updated and reflect the updated account &amp; billing information.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Personal Video Recording (PVR)</span></strong></span></span></p>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:square\">\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Activation of PVR:</strong>&nbsp; PVR features are currently free and will be automatically activated for all our subscribers with valid subscription.</span></span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Watching recorded contents:</strong> </span></span></span>\n	<ul style=\"list-style-type:square\">\n		<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">If subscriber&rsquo;s subscription is expired, he won&rsquo;t be able to watch the recorded contents just like he cannot watch live TV. He will need to recharge his required subscription amount in order to watch his previously recorded contents again.</span></span></span></li>\n		<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Recorded contents are encrypted &amp; therefore can only be watched in the STB where it has been recorded. If subscribers insert the USB storage device to laptops, mobiles, personal computers, STBs of other operators or even other STBs of AKASH, he won&rsquo;t be able to play the recorded contents.</span></span></span></li>\n		<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Auto deletion of recorded contents will not happen unless subscribers do it on their own. However, Factory reset or formatting the USB storage device will erase the recording contents.</span></span></span></li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>USB Storage Device:</strong> Any FAT32 format pen drive or external Hard disk drive can be inserted through the USB port of the STB in order to record contents. However, it is recommended that maximum 500 GB capacity USB Storage devices are used. Also when a drive is inserted first time, it might request to format the drive. Therefore, customers are recommended to insert a drive containing no other files except previous recording files of AKASH.</span></span></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">When you insert your drive, the STB may require it to be formatted in order to make it ready for recording storage. Therefore, you are advised to take care of your existing files before you insert the drive into your STB because formatting will erase all existing files.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Furthermore, if you record a program, then remove the drive and insert it in any other devices, and then reinsert the drive into the same STB, the STB may require the drive to be formatted again in order to make it ready for recording storage.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Also, if you use the pen drive (where recorded item is stored) to store other files, the other files will get encrypted and you&#39;ll not be able to open/view the encrypted file in any devices. Therefore, it is recommended to use a dedicated pen drive/USB Storage device for recording purpose only.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:square\">\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Live TV Pause:</strong> Customer will need to enable it from &ldquo;Recording Settings&rdquo;. </span></span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Instant Recording:</strong> It can be done anytime with the record button from the remote.</span></span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Schedule Recording:</strong> It can be done from both &ldquo;Program Guide&rdquo; menu and &ldquo;Recording&rdquo; menu. </span></span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Recording Conflicts:</strong> </span></span></span>\n	<ul style=\"list-style-type:square\">\n		<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">While one channel is being recorded, subscribers can only switch to other channels if those are in the same transponder (of the satellite) of the channel which is being recorded. If they attempt to switch to other channels, they will get a pop up message on their screen and they&#39;ll need to stop the ongoing recording in order to switch to channels from other transponders.</span></span></span></li>\n		<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">While recording is on-going, the STB needs to be switched on. If the STB is in standby mode when a scheduled recording starts, the STB will automatically wake up from standby in order to execute the scheduled recording.</span></span></span></li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:100.0%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"background-color:#d9d9d9; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; height:20px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">SN</span></strong></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"background-color:#d9d9d9; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; height:20px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Category</span></strong></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"background-color:#d9d9d9; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; height:20px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Topic</span></strong></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"background-color:#d9d9d9; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; height:20px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Question</span></strong></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"background-color:#d9d9d9; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; height:20px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Answer</span></strong></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:160px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">1</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:160px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">UI</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:160px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Enhanced UI Look &amp; Feel</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:160px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">I&#39;ve recently noticed that the look and feel of my screen UI have been changed. Why has it happened?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:160px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Dear Subscriber, AKASH always strives to bring the best for you. In order to provide you a brand new feel of our UI, we&#39;ve recently enhanced it and that is why you are seeing the difference on your screen! Hope you will love it! It is to be noted that no major functionality has been changed apart from the introduction of Personal Video Recording features. Our UI is as convenient as always along with the new enhanced look &amp; feel and the recording features! Enjoy the magical experience of AKASH!</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">2</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">UI</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Standby Settings</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">After how many hours, the STB will go to standby mode automatically?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">After 3 hours of continuous viewing with no remote control operation, the STB will automatically go to Standby mode.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">3</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">UI</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Standby Settings</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">How can I change the default standby settings?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Please go to &quot;Standby Settings&quot; from &quot;My Settings&quot; menu and select the preferable duration of &quot;Auto Standby&quot;. If you want, you can select &quot;Off&quot; to disable auto-standby feature.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:160px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">4</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:160px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">UI</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:160px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">New Features</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:160px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">What are the new features of this enhanced UI?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:160px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Apart from the brand new attractive designs, there are new features like &quot;Genre Listing&quot;. From &quot;Program Guide&quot;, you can see the genres of channels, and thus you can selectively view the program guide of the selected genre&#39;s channels only. Also, the &quot;Help&quot; page has been upgraded. Now you can see your Subscriber Name, Registered Mobile Number (RMN), Activated Packages, Base Package Expiry, Account Balance, etc. information easily on the &quot;Help&quot; menu by clicking the &quot;Help&quot; button from your remote.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">5</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">UI</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">New Features</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">I see there&#39;s wrong info about my account (i.e: Name, RMN, Package, etc.) on the help page. What can I do?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Please call our call center at 16442 in order to correct your account information upon providing your Sub ID &amp; other required info.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:180px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">6</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:180px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:180px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR Activation</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:180px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">How can I activate recording features in my Set-Top Box?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:180px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Dear Subscriber, we are delighted to inform you that AKASH has introduced Personal Video Recording (PVR) features for you! Now you can instantly record your favorite programs, schedule recordings, and pause live TV programs! And all of these exciting features are completely free for you! It is to be noted that you will need to insert an external hard disk or pen drive (a maximum of 500 GB is recommended) through the USB port of your Set-Top Box (STB) in order to enjoy these features.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">7</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR Activation</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">I have inserted the USB device and enabled settings from recording settings. But when I attempt to record it says that I haven&#39;t subscribed to personal video recording features. What can I do?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Please call our call center at 16442 in order to resolve this issue.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">8</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">USB Device Management</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Where can I see the remaining storage and used storage sizes of my device?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Please go to the &quot;Storage Management&quot; option from the &quot;Recording Settings&quot; menu in order to access the required information.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">9</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">USB Device Management</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">What kind of USB devices can I use for recording features?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">You can insert any pendrive or external hard disk if those are in FAT32 file format. The recommended device storage capacity of the USB device is up to 500 GB.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:300px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">10</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:300px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:300px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">USB Device Management</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:300px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If I insert my USB Drive/Pendrive/Hard disk, the STB requires to format it. What can I do about it?<br />\n			<br />\n			If I use one drive/pen drive for recording, can I use it for other purposes?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:300px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">When you insert your drive, the STB may require it to be formatted in order to make it ready for recording storage. Therefore, you are advised to take care of your existing files before you insert the drive into your STB because formatting will erase all existing files.<br />\n			Furthermore, if you record a program, then remove the drive and insert it in any other devices, and then reinsert the drive into the same STB,&nbsp; the STB may require the drive to be formatted again in order to make it ready for recording storage.<br />\n			<br />\n			Also, if you use the pen drive (where the recorded item is stored) to store other files, the other files will get encrypted and you&#39;ll not be able to open/view the encrypted file in any device. Therefore, it is recommended to use a dedicated pen drive/USB Storage device for recording purposes only.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:100px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">11</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:100px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:100px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">USB Device Management</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:100px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">What&#39;s the size (GB/MB) of 1-hour program recording?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:100px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">It&nbsp;depends on the type of program and other factors.<br />\n			<br />\n			Approximately for 1 hour of SD (Standard Definition) recording it can take 0.7 to 0.9 GB &amp; for 1 hour of HD (High Definition) recording it can take 1 to 1.2 GB. These are mere recommendations only. </span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:220px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">12</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:220px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:220px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Live TV Pause</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:220px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">How can I pause &quot;Live TV&quot;?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:220px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you have already&nbsp;inserted an external USB storage device in your STB then you are almost there! If otherwise please perform this activity&nbsp;first.<br />\n			<br />\n			After that just go to &quot;Recording settings&quot; from your &quot;Recording&quot; menu and then select &quot;enable&quot; in the &quot;Live TV Pause&quot; option. Now you can enjoy our exciting &quot;Live TV Pause&quot; feature just by clicking the pause button from your AKASH remote whenever you want during your favorite programs! After pausing, you can use the forward, rewind button, play, etc. to skim through the program after you have paused it. </span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">13</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Live TV Pause</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">How can I return to live TV telecast from the &quot;Live TV Pause&quot; mode?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you want to switch to Live TV telecast from the pause mode, press the &quot;exit&quot; or &quot;stop&quot; button, and then you&#39;ll be redirected to the current live broadcast of the channel.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:1.25in\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">14</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:1.25in\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:1.25in\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Recording settings</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:1.25in\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">What does it mean by &quot;Rewind duration&quot;?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:1.25in\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;Rewind Duration&quot; is a setting needed for the &quot;Live TV Pause&quot; feature. When Live TV Pause is &quot;enabled&quot;, your Set-Top Box (STB) continuously maintains a buffer recording for a specific duration; a duration within which you can go back &amp; forward after you&#39;ve paused live TV. This specific duration is the &quot;Rewind Duration&quot;. It is set to 30:00 min by default and you can change it to a maximum of 59:59 min.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:80px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">15</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:80px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:80px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Recording settings</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:80px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">What is &quot;Rewind Interval&quot;?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:80px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">When you have paused live TV, you have the ability to fast forward or rewind through the &quot;Rewind Duration&quot; time span. &quot;Rewind interval&quot; is the duration of each step of fast forwarding or rewinding you do. It can be selected in min: sec format.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:260px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">16</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:260px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:260px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Recording settings</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:260px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">What is &quot;Start Record Earlier&quot; &amp; &quot;End Record Later&quot;?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:260px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;Start Record Earlier&quot; &amp; &quot;End Record Later&quot; are very much useful for the &quot;Schedule Recording&quot; feature. You can schedule a program to be recorded from our program guide. Now, for example, the program guide shows the program will air from 7:00 PM to 7:30 PM. Therefore, if you schedule the recording from there, your recording will be done for the exact time span of the program mentioned in the program guide. Now, if you want to stretch the recording let&#39;s say from 6:50 to 7:40 because you want to ensure you don&#39;t miss any part of the program, you can select 10 minutes in &quot;Start Record Earlier&quot; &amp; 10 minutes in &quot;End Record Later&quot;. Therefore, your scheduled program will be recorded beyond the program schedule mentioned in the program guide, up to your wish! So, these 2 settings help you to stretch your recording beyond the specified time span mentioned in program guides. </span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">17</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Recording settings</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">When my recording is going on, there&#39;s an icon on screen always. I want to get rid of that. How can I do that?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">We always want to bring every bit of convenience to you! You can do that very easily through our user menu! Just go to &quot;Recording Settings&quot; and select &quot;off&quot; for the &quot;Show Recording Icon&quot; option.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:200px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">18</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:200px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:200px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Instant Recording</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:200px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">How can I do Instant Recording?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:200px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you have already inserted an external USB storage device in your STB then you are almost there! If otherwise please perform this&nbsp;activity&nbsp;first.<br />\n			<br />\n			<br />\n			After that just press&nbsp;the record button from your AKASH remote and instant recording of your favorite program will be started! When you want to stop the recording, please press the blue colored stop button from your AKASH remote and the recording will be stopped and it will be saved in your &quot;Recorded List&quot; under &quot;Recording&quot; in the Menu.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:300px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">19</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:300px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:300px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Schedule Recording</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:300px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">How can I do Schedule Recording?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:300px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you have already inserted an external USB storage device in your STB then you are almost there! If otherwise please perform this&nbsp;activity&nbsp;first.</span></span></span><br />\n			<br />\n			<br />\n			<span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">After that you are good to go for schedule recordings! On AKASH you can do schedule recordings in 2 ways. You can do it from our &quot;Program Guide&quot;. Just skim through the program guide and whenever you want you can press the blue button as specified on the screen of the program guide page on your favorite program and recording will be scheduled very easily!<br />\n			<br />\n			<br />\n			<br />\n			In addition to that, you have another way to do it. You can just go to &quot;Recording&quot; menu and then select &quot;Schedule Recording&quot; and then enter the appropriate inputs in order to schedule recordings also. </span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">20</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Recorded Contents</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">From where can I access the programs I&#39;ve recorded?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:40px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">All your recorded contents can be found in &quot;Recorded List&quot; under the &quot;Recording&quot; menu.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:80px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">21</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:80px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:80px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Recorded Contents</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:80px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">I currently do not have balance in my account/my subscription has expired and I cannot watch the contents that I have recorded. What can I do?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:80px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Dear Subscriber, you need a valid subscription in order to watch live TV programs as well as all your previously recorded contents. Please recharge your subscription amount and then you&#39;ll be able to watch your recorded programs.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:180px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">22</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:180px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:180px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Recording Modalities</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:180px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">A recording was going on and I tried to switch to another channel but I could not. What can I do?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:180px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">As you know, we broadcast our services through Bangbandhu Satellite 1 &amp; all our channels are distributed among different transponders of Bangbandhu Satellite 1. All channels are divided into different clusters. When one channel is being recorded, you can only switch to other channels if those are in the same transponder as the transponder of the channel which is being recorded. If you attempt to switch to other channels, you will get a pop up message on your screen and you will need to stop the ongoing recording in order to switch to channels from other transponders.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">23</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Recording Modalities</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Can I watch the recorded contents in other devices/Laptop/PC/Mobile/Other STB/Other AKASH STB?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">No, you can only watch your recorded contents in your STB as the recorded contents are encrypted and will only work with the STB the program was recorded with.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">24</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Recording Modalities</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If I record a channel which has multiple audios (i.e.: Travel XP has both Bangla &amp; English), which audio track will be recorded along with the video?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Both audio tracks will be recorded! And you can switch audios during the playback by pressing the audio button from your remote.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:100px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">25</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:100px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:100px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Recording Modalities</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:100px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Can I keep my TV switched off during a scheduled recording is on-going?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:100px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">You can keep your TV switched off or it can be in sleep mode/standby mode. Your STB can also be in standby mode during the scheduled time, however, your STB power must be switched on meaning you cannot switch off the power supply to your STB. Otherwise the STB won&#39;t be able to perform the recording you&#39;ve scheduled. </span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:100px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">26</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:100px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:100px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Recording Modalities</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:100px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">I recorded a content for &quot;X&quot; seconds (below 2 mins) and when I try to play it back, the screen becomes black and nothing is played.</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:100px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Dear Subscriber, you might face some issues in playing recorded contents which are less than 2 minutes in length. Therefore, we recommend you to ensure that your recordings are minimum of 2 minutes in duration so those issues do not occur. Thank you for your understanding!</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:80px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">27</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:80px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">PVR</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:80px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Recording Modalities</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:80px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">When I&#39;m playing a recorded content and try to change the audio language track during the playback, sometimes the video jumps forward for few seconds. What can I do to solve this?</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:80px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Dear Subscriber, when you change the audio track, it requires a few seconds to sync with the video track. Therefore, you might face some issues in the playback. We apologize for the inconvenience. Thank you for your understanding!</span></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '1595863626-12021104.png', '1595863626-20740886.png', '', 'Product', 0, 0, 1, '2020-07-20 01:55:57', '2030-08-16 11:20:34', '2020-07-28 22:26:10', '2020-07-19 11:48:54', '', 121);
INSERT INTO `offers` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `description`, `thumb_image`, `banner_image`, `app_image`, `tags`, `show_in_app`, `show_buy_btn`, `state`, `start_time`, `end_time`, `updatedOn`, `createdOn`, `uda`, `serial`) VALUES
(26, 'Cashback Campaign August’20', 'cashback-august-20', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">After buying a new AKASH connection, activating and recharging for a month, you would get a cashback equivalent to the recharge amount BDT 399/249 for the subscribed package. The cashback amount would be given in your AKASH account. </span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\"><strong>Campaign Duration:</strong> 16<sup>th</sup> August, 2020 -31<sup>st</sup> August, 2020</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\"> </span></span></p>\n\n<h1><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Calibri Light\",sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#2e74b5\"><strong>Terms & Conditions</strong></span></span></span></h1>\n\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">All individuals (without any special contracts) are considered eligible for this cashback campaign while purchasing a new connection in the campaign period. </span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">If a customer after purchasing AKASH connection at the end of the free trial period (5 days) avails AKASH Standard package s/he will get BDT 399 cashback & if he avails AKASH Lite package, s/he will get BDT 249 Cashback in his AKASH account.</span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">Customers buying multiple connections will be eligible for multiple cash back according to the packages he is adopting at the time of purchase/account creation.</span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">The Cashback will be disbursed to the Subscriber’s AKASH account by 10 working days. </span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">A subscriber will get the maximum Cashback amount of BDT 399 for AKASH Standard and BDT 249 for AKASH Lite. </span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">Subscriber groups enjoying reduced product prices (STB/CPE) will not be eligible for this cashback offer. (i.e: Employee, employee fnf, group employee, dealer, etc.)</span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">Corporate entities which are our subscribers by contracts/ are in invoicing relations or in rental modalities/models are not eligible for this offer.</span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">To be eligible for cashback, the customer will need to buy a new connection & recharge at least 1 month’s equivalent subscription amount after his/her purchase & within the campaign period. However, as customer buying on the last day of the campaign may need time for set-up and activation, therefore he/she can recharge up to the 7th of September to get the offer.</span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">Customers purchasing AKASH connection before 16th August 2020, but activating during the campaign period (16<sup>th</sup> August, 2020 -31<sup>st</sup> August, 2020) will not be eligible for the campaign. </span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">The cashback amount can be used for consumption in packages, add on packs, etc. as permitted by AKASH.</span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">The validity of the cashback amount will expire within 3 months after the disbursement date of Cashback. </span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">AKASH (Beximco Communications Ltd.) assures its customers/subscribers that, there is no financial investment, deposit, security money required to enter Cashback Campaign August’20, all the customers/subscribers are requested to remain cautious for any such type of fraudulent offer. (Beximco Communications Ltd. won’t be responsible for any kind of personal or financial loss due to any fraudulent incident)</span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">By participating, the subscriber/ purchaser agrees to be bound by these Terms & Conditions. Subscriber /purchaser must comply with these Terms & Conditions to be able to receive the cashback from this campaign. </span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">AKASH (Beximco Communications Ltd.) reserves all the right to change, extend, and cancel the offer at any time.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\"> </span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\"> FAQ</span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\"><strong> </strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\"> </span></span></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:100.0%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"background-color:#d9d9d9; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:none; border-top:1px solid black; height:40px; vertical-align:bottom; width:2%px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\"> </span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"background-color:#d9d9d9; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; height:40px; vertical-align:top; width:20%px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\"><strong>FAQ</strong></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"background-color:#d9d9d9; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; height:40px; vertical-align:top; width:76%px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\"><strong>Answers </strong></span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:88px; vertical-align:top; width:2%px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:right\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">1</span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:88px; vertical-align:top; width:20%px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">What is Cashback Campaign August\'20?</span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:88px; vertical-align:top; width:76%px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">AKASH always strives to make the AKASH experience the most rewarding. In this August \'20, anyone who buys a new AKASH Connection from our authorized retail outlets, direct sales and online within Bangladesh between 16- 31 August 2020, activates and recharges for a month would get a cashback equivalent to the recharge amount BDT 399/249 for the subscribed package that s/he has subscribed after the end of the free trial period of 5 days. The cashback amount would be given in his AKASH account. </span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:41px; vertical-align:top; width:2%px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:right\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">2</span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:41px; vertical-align:top; width:20%px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">How long is the duration of this Cashback Campaign August\'20?</span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:41px; vertical-align:top; width:76%px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">The Cashback Campaign August\'20 is valid from 16<sup>th</sup> August, 2020 -31<sup>st</sup> August, 2020</span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:71px; vertical-align:top; width:2%px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:right\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">3</span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:71px; vertical-align:top; width:20%px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">If I purchase only STB, will I be eligible to pay the price of Cashback Campaign August\'20?</span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:71px; vertical-align:top; width:76%px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">YES! On purchasing a new connection (within the campaign period 16<sup>th</sup> August, 2020 -31<sup>st</sup> August, 2020), activating and recharging for a month customer would get a cashback equivalent to the recharge amount of BDT 399/249 for the subscribed package that s/he has subscribed after the end of the free trial period of 5 days. The cashback amount would be given in his AKASH account. </span></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:106px; vertical-align:top; width:2%px\">\n			<p style=\"text-align:right\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">4</span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:106px; vertical-align:top; width:20%px\">\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif\">I\'m a current subscriber of AKASH. Am I eligible to participate in the Cashback Campaign  August\'20?</span></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:106px; vertical-align:top; width:7